  solution    : "Configurar auditoria imutável"
  reference   : "Referência completa no Baseline HITSS."
  see_also    : "https://www.debian.org/doc/manuals/securing-debian-manual/"
  cmd         : "bash -c '( auditctl -s 2>/dev/null | grep -Eq '\"'\"'^[[:space:]]*enabled[[:space:]]+2\\b'\"'\"' ) && echo \"PASS\" || echo \"FAIL\"'"
  expect      : "(?i)^\s*pass\s*$"
</custom_item>

<custom_item>
  type        : CMD_EXEC
  description : "182, AIDE instalado e inicializado, Alta"
  info        : "Garantir AIDE instalado e base inicializada"
  solution    : "Garantir AIDE instalado e base inicializada"
  reference   : "Referência completa no Baseline HITSS para Debian."
  see_also    : "https://www.debian.org/doc/manuals/securing-debian-manual/"
  cmd         : "bash -c 'pkg_installed() { dpkg-query -W -f='\"'\"'${Status}'\"'\"' \"$1\" 2>/dev/null | grep -q '\"'\"'install ok installed'\"'\"'; }; ( pkg_installed aide && [ -f /var/lib/aide/aide.db.gz ] ) && echo \"PASS\" || echo \"FAIL\"'"
  expect      : "(?i)^\s*pass\s*$"
</custom_item>

<custom_item>
  type        : CMD_EXEC
  description : "183, Verificação integridade, Alta"
  info        : "Garante agendamento recorrente de verificação com AIDE."
  solution    : "Agendar verificação periódica de integridade."
  reference   : "Referência completa no Baseline HITSS para Debian."
  see_also    : "https://www.debian.org/doc/manuals/securing-debian-manual/"
  cmd         : "bash -c '( grep -Ersq '\"'\"'aide(\\.wrapper)? .*(--check|--update|\\$AIDEARGS)'\"'\"' /etc/cron.* /etc/crontab /var/spool/cron 2>/dev/null || systemctl list-timers --all 2>/dev/null | grep -qi aide ) && echo \"PASS\" || echo \"FAIL\"'"
  expect      : "(?i)^\s*pass\s*$"
</custom_item>

<custom_item>
  type        : CMD_EXEC
  description : "184, Protecao dos binarios de auditoria, Alta"
  info        : "Proteger binarios e ferramentas de auditoria"
  solution    : "Proteger binarios e ferramentas de auditoria"
  reference   : "Referência completa no Baseline HITSS para Debian."
  see_also    : "https://www.debian.org/doc/manuals/securing-debian-manual/"
  cmd         : "bash -c '( for b in auditctl aureport ausearch autrace auditd augenrules; do p=\"$(command -v \"$b\")\" || exit 1; stat -Lc \"%U %G\" \"$p\" | awk '\"'\"'{if($1!=\"root\" || $2!=\"root\") exit 1}'\"'\"' || exit 1; done ) && echo \"PASS\" || echo \"FAIL\"'"
  expect      : "(?i)^\s*pass\s*$"
</custom_item>

<custom_item>
  type        : CMD_EXEC
  description : "185, Permissões passwd, Alta"
  info        : "Protege o arquivo principal de contas locais contra alteração indevida."
  solution    : "Ajustar permissões de /etc/passwd."
  reference   : "Referência completa no Baseline HITSS para Debian."
  see_also    : "https://www.debian.org/doc/manuals/securing-debian-manual/"
  cmd         : "bash -c '( [ -f /etc/passwd ] && stat -Lc \"%a %u %g\" /etc/passwd | grep -Eq '\"'\"'^64[0-9] 0 0$'\"'\"' ) && echo \"PASS\" || echo \"FAIL\"'"
  expect      : "(?i)^\s*pass\s*$"
</custom_item>

<custom_item>
  type        : CMD_EXEC
  description : "186, Permissões passwd-, Baixa"
